257.090.  Court to call election — contents of call. — 1.  Upon designation of the election districts the court shall call for the referendum and board election accordingly.
  2.  The call for the referendum and first board election shall specify also at least the following:
  (1)  The purpose of the district as organized by the court;
  (2)  The general area of the district;
  (3)  The qualification of voters;
  (4)  The vote required for passage of the referendum;
  (5)  The basis of representation provided herein for the election of trustees, and the filing time for candidates for the board of trustees.
(L. 1959 S.B. 199 § 9, A.L. 1978 H.B. 971)
